      "id": "slide_02",
      "type": "concept_teaching",
      "title": "The Power of Transitions",
      "duration_estimate": 240,
      "content": {
        "heading": "Why Transitions Matter",
        "text": "Transitions show relationships between ideas and help readers follow your logic. Without them, writing feels choppy and disconnected.",
        "concept_box": {
          "title": "Types of Transition Relationships",
          "points": [
            "‚ûï **Addition** - Furthermore, additionally, moreover, also",
            "üîÑ **Contrast** - However, nevertheless, on the other hand, yet",
            "üìà **Cause/Effect** - Therefore, consequently, as a result, thus",
            "üìù **Example** - For instance, specifically, namely, such as"
          ]
        },
        "examples": {
          "without": "Solar energy is renewable. It reduces carbon emissions. It saves money on electricity bills.",
          "with": "Solar energy is renewable. Furthermore, it reduces carbon emissions and saves money on electricity bills."
        }
      },
      "interactions": [
        {
          "type": "reveal_on_click",
          "elements": [
            {
              "trigger": "Click to see the difference",
              "reveal": "Notice how 'Furthermore' connects the ideas and shows they're building on each other, rather than just listing separate facts."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "slide_03",
      "type": "strategy_teaching",
      "title": "The FLOW Method for Transitions",
      "duration_estimate": 300,
      "content": {
        "heading": "Strategy: Create Seamless Connections",
        "strategy_steps": [
          {
            "step": 1,
            "title": "FOLLOW the logic",
            "description": "Identify the relationship between ideas",
            "example": "Idea 1: Exercise improves health. Idea 2: It reduces stress. ‚Üí Addition relationship"
          },
          {
            "step": 2,
            "title": "LOCATE the best transition",
            "description": "Choose words that match the logical relationship",
            "example": "Addition: Additionally, exercise reduces stress and improves mental well-being."
          },
          {
            "step": 3,
            "title": "ORDER for maximum impact",
            "description": "Place transitions where they'll guide readers most effectively",
            "example": "Usually at the beginning of sentences or paragraphs for clear signaling"
          },
          {
            "step": 4,
            "title": "WEAVE naturally",
            "description": "Ensure transitions feel organic, not forced",
            "example": "Avoid overusing transitions - sometimes ideas connect naturally without them"
          }
        ],
        "memory_aid": "Keep your writing in good **F.L.O.W.**!"
      },
      "interactions": [
        {
          "type": "step_by_step_reveal",
          "auto_advance": false
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "slide_04",
      "type": "concept_teaching",
      "title": "Advanced Transition Strategies",
      "duration_estimate": 280,
      "content": {
        "heading": "Beyond Basic Connectors",
        "text": "Sophisticated transitions do more than connect - they clarify relationships and enhance meaning.",
        "concept_box": {
          "title": "Advanced Techniques",
          "points": [
            "üîó **Transitional phrases** - In light of this evidence, Given these circumstances",
            "üìç **Referential transitions** - This approach, Such strategies, These findings",
            "‚è±Ô∏è **Temporal markers** - Meanwhile, Subsequently, Before long, Eventually",
            "üéØ **Emphasis transitions** - Indeed, In fact, Notably, Most importantly"
          ]
        },
        "examples": {
          "basic": "The experiment failed. However, we learned valuable lessons.",
          "advanced": "The experiment failed to produce expected results. This setback, however, provided valuable insights into the underlying mechanisms."
        }
      },
      "interactions": [
